cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the use of algorithms to analyze big datasets for medical monitoring, which falls under the category of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of phone data for diagnostics and monitoring, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the evaluation of algorithms for monitoring mental wellbeing, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a solution to reduce systematic errors in the evaluation of personalized medical monitoring, which falls under the category of social and information networks, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category.
